  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening National and Local Disaster Preparedness and Response Capacities in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 2020, Uganda has seen an increase in raising water levels of most major bodies of water, affecting communities around Lake Albert, Lake Victoria, Lake Kyoga, and Lake Kwania, and the Nile River (Uganda). This significantly impacts the fishing communities and landing site, including public infrastructure. Through this project, IOM coordinates with the Office of the Prime Minister, the Red Cross, and other humanitarian actors through its Displacement Tracking Matrix tools. IOM is building this coalition in order to aggregate data on the specific caseload for the design of durable and appropriate response actions. IOM works with the National Emergency Coordination and Operations Centre under the Office of the Prime Minister which is mandated to collect and disseminate early warning information, maintain a national disaster database, provide guidance to various organizations and stakeholders on handling an emergency or disaster, and establish and coordinate emergency rapid disaster response teams.</narrative>
  </description>
